value.value: Abnormal flatness (decreased height) of epiphyses.
An abnormally increased calcium concentration in the blood.
Reduction in the concentration of albumin in the blood.
An increased concentration of glucose in the blood.
An increased concentration of glucose in the urine.

definition.value: Glycosuria, the excretion of abnormal amounts of glucose in the urine, generally results in osmotic diuresis.

value.value: An elevated lipid concentration in the blood.

definition.value: Hyperlipidemia is an elevation of the blood levels of lipids including primarily cholesterol, phospholipids and triglycerides and cholesterol esters. The lipids are transported on lipoproteins some of which are commonly used for clinical measurements, including chylomicrons, very-low density lipoproteins (VLDL), intermediate-density lipoproteins (IDL), low-density lipoproteins, and high-density lipoproteins (HDL).

value.value: Small hands and feet.
An increased concentration of glycine in the urine.

definition.value: Normal urinary glycine total (free and combined form) excretion is around 450 mg per 24 hours.

value.value: An abnormality of the composition of urine or the levels of its components.
Abnormality of the homeostasis (concentration) of a monoatomic ion.
Concentration of a hormone in the blood circulation outside of normal limits.
Any deviation from the normal concentration of a lipid in the blood circulation.

definition.value: According to CHEBI:18059 'Lipids' is a loosely defined term for substances of biological origin that are soluble in nonpolar solvents. They consist of saponifiable lipids, such as glycerides (fats and oils) and phospholipids, as well as nonsaponifiable lipids, principally steroids.

value.value: A contracture (chronic loss of joint motion due to structural changes in muscle, tendons, ligaments, or skin) that prevent normal movement of one or more joints of the limbs.
An increased concentration of cholesterol in the blood.

Reduced activity of coagulation factor VIII. Factor VIII (fVIII) is a cofactor in the intrinsic clotting cascade that is activated to fVIIIa in the presence of minute quantities of thrombin. fVIIIa acts as a receptor, for factors IXa and X.
An abnormally decreased calcium concentration in the urine.
An abnormal buildup of lactic acid in the body, leading to acidification of the blood and other bodily fluids.

definition.value: Note that the term acidemia is used to describe the state of low pH in the blood, whereas acidosis is used to describe the processes that lead to acidemia. In medical jargon, however, the two terms are used interchangeably.

value.value: An increased amount of nitrogen in the form of urea in the blood.
An decreased concentration of cholesterol in the blood.
The concentration of glutaric acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.
An abnormal increased in the concentration of corticotropin, also known as adrenocorticotropic hormone (ACTH), in the blood.
Abnormally increased serum levels of alkaline phosphatase activity.
An increased concentration of 5-aminolevulinic acid (CHEBI:17549) in the urine.

definition.value: Delta-aminolevulinic acid synthesis is a rate-controlling step in heme synthesis.

value.value: Intrapelvic bulging of the medial acetabular wall.

definition.value: Protrusion of the acetabulum, which is the socket that together with the head of the femur forms the hip joint. The protrusion is the result of increased depth of the socket and results in medial displacement of the femoral head.

value.value: Underdevelopment of the breast.
Distance from nasion to subnasale more than two standard deviations below the mean, or alternatively, an apparently decreased length from the nasal root to the nasal tip.

definition.value: Note: a small nose has both decreased height and a decreased width. These should be coded separately.

value.value: A disorder of muscle unrelated to impairment of innervation or neuromuscular junction.

definition.value: The diagnosis of myopathy is often confirmed on the basis of myopathic changes in muscle biopsy.

value.value: The presence of skeletal muscular atrophy (which is also known as amyotrophy).
An abnormally increased overall level of immunoglobulin E in blood.
Decreased activity of coagulation factor V.

definition.value: Factor V is activated to factor Va by means of minute amounts of thrombin (and inactivated by larger amounts of thrombin). Activated factor V (fVa) is a cofactor in the formation of the prothrombinase complex.

value.value: An abnormally increased sodium concentration in the blood.
An increased concentration of tyrosine in the blood.
An decreased concentration of high-density lipoprotein cholesterol in the blood.
Concentration of carnitine in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

definition.value: Carnitine is responsible for the transport of fatty acids from the cytosol into the mitochondria.

value.value: An elevation of the level of the enzyme creatine kinase (also known as creatine phosphokinase (CK; EC 2.7.3.2) in the blood. CK levels can be elevated in a number of clinical disorders such as myocardial infarction, rhabdomyolysis, and muscular dystrophy.

definition.value: 'has part' some ('increased amount' and ('inheres in' some (IMR_0002602 and ('part of' some blood))) and ('has modifier' some abnormal))

value.value: Location of the urethral opening on the inferior aspect of the penis.

label.value: Gonadal tissue inappropriate for external genitalia or chromosomal sex

value.value: Aplasia of the vagina.
Distention of the abdomen.

definition.value: Abdominal distention can be a secondary feature associated with a number of conditions such as bowel obstruction.

value.value: Underdeveloped acetabulae.
Abnormally reduced serum levels of alkaline phosphatase.
A functional anomaly of mitochondria.
The closed form of spina bifida with incomplete closure of a vertebral body with intact overlying skin.
Reduced ability to move the vertebral column with a resulting limitation of neck and trunk flexion.
Abnormally increased curvature (anterior concavity) of the lumbar or cervical spine.

label.value: Abnormal form of the vertebral bodies
